---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Healthcare Eligibility"
  description="Learn about eligibility for Medi-Cal, Covered California, Medicare, and other healthcare programs in the Bay Area."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav class="mb-6 text-sm" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/eligibility" class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >Eligibility Guides</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="text-neutral-400">/</li>
            <li class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">Healthcare</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          Healthcare Programs
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-8">
          California offers several programs to help you get health coverage, including free
          coverage for low-income residents, subsidized marketplace plans, and programs for seniors.
        </p>

        <!-- Legal Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only and is not legal
            or professional advice. Eligibility requirements may vary by individual circumstances, and
            additional requirements may apply. To determine your actual eligibility, please apply directly
            to the program. Information is subject to change without notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Medi-Cal Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Medi-Cal
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— California's Free Health Insurance (Medicaid)</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Medi-Cal is California's version of Medicaid — free or low-cost health coverage for
            low-income residents. It covers doctor visits, hospital care, prescriptions, mental
            health, dental, and more at little or no cost to you.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Income Limits (2026)
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Adults (19-64):</strong> Up to $21,597/year individual, $44,367/year family
                of 4 (138% FPL)
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Children (0-18):</strong> Up to $85,519/year family of 4 (266% FPL)</li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Pregnant women:</strong> Up to $45,050/year if single (213% FPL)
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Seniors/Disabled:</strong> Similar to adult limits, with some variations
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Asset Limits (2026)</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Individual: $130,000</li>
              <li>• Each additional household member: +$65,000</li>
              <li class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400">
                (Home, one vehicle, and retirement accounts generally not counted)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>2026 Immigration Changes:</strong> Adults applying after January 1, 2026 with unsatisfactory
              immigration status receive restricted Medi-Cal (emergency/pregnancy only). Children and
              pregnant individuals remain eligible for full-scope regardless of status.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • Online: <a
                href="https://www.coveredca.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">CoveredCA.com</a
              > or <a
                href="https://benefitscal.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">BenefitsCal.com</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • Phone: <a
                href="tel:1-800-300-1506"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">1-800-300-1506</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• In person: Your county social services office</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Covered California Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Covered California
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Subsidized Health Insurance (ACA/"Obamacare" Marketplace)</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Covered California is the state's health insurance marketplace where you can buy private
            insurance, often with government help to lower your costs. If you earn too much for free
            Medi-Cal but still need help affording coverage, this is likely your best option.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Who Qualifies for Subsidies
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Income above Medi-Cal limits but need help with premiums</li>
              <li>• No affordable employer coverage available</li>
              <li>• U.S. citizen or lawfully present immigrant</li>
              <li>• California resident</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Subsidy Examples</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Premium Tax Credits:</strong> Lower your monthly payment based on income
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Cost-Sharing Reductions:</strong> Lower deductibles and copays (Silver plans)
              </li>
              <li>• Many Bay Area residents pay $0-50/month with subsidies</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Enrollment Periods</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• <strong>Open Enrollment:</strong> November 1 - January 31 each year</li>
            <li>
              • <strong>Special Enrollment:</strong> After qualifying life events (job loss, move, marriage,
              baby)
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • Online: <a
                href="https://www.coveredca.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">CoveredCA.com</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • Phone: <a
                href="tel:1-800-300-1506"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">1-800-300-1506</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• Free help from certified enrollment counselors</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Medicare Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Medicare
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Health Insurance for Seniors (65+) and Some Disabled</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Medicare is the federal health insurance program primarily for people 65 and older.
            Unlike Medi-Cal (which is based on income), Medicare is mainly based on age and work
            history. Some younger people with disabilities also qualify.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Who Qualifies</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Age 65 or older</li>
              <li>• Under 65 with certain disabilities (after 24 months of SSDI)</li>
              <li>• Any age with End-Stage Renal Disease (ESRD) or ALS</li>
              <li>• Must be U.S. citizen or permanent resident (5+ years)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Medicare Parts</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Part A (Hospital):</strong> Usually premium-free if you worked 10+ years
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Part B (Medical):</strong> Monthly premium (~$175/month in 2026)</li>
              <li>• <strong>Part C (Medicare Advantage):</strong> Private plan alternative</li>
              <li>• <strong>Part D (Prescription):</strong> Drug coverage, separate premium</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>Low-income?</strong> You may qualify for both Medicare and Medi-Cal (Medi-Medi),
              which helps pay premiums and out-of-pocket costs. Also check the Medicare Savings Programs
              and Extra Help for prescriptions.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Enroll</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • Online: <a
                href="https://www.medicare.gov"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">Medicare.gov</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • Phone: <a
                href="tel:1-800-633-4227"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >1-800-MEDICARE (1-800-633-4227)</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• Social Security office</li>
            <li>• Free help from HICAP (Health Insurance Counseling)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Mental Health & Crisis Services -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Mental Health & Crisis Services
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Mental health services are available regardless of insurance or ability to pay.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Crisis Lines</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline:</strong> Call or text <a
                  href="tel:988"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">988</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Crisis Text Line:</strong> Text HOME to 741741</li>
              <li>
                • <strong>SF Mobile Crisis:</strong>
                <a
                  href="tel:415-970-4000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">415-970-4000</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              County Behavioral Health
            </h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              Each county provides mental health services to Medi-Cal members and uninsured
              residents:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Counseling and therapy</li>
              <li>• Psychiatric services</li>
              <li>• Substance use treatment</li>
              <li>• Crisis intervention</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Community Health Centers -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Community Health Centers
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Federally Qualified Health Centers (FQHCs) provide care to everyone regardless of
            insurance or ability to pay. Fees are based on a sliding scale.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Services Available</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Primary care and preventive services</li>
              <li>• Dental care</li>
              <li>• Mental health counseling</li>
              <li>• Prescription assistance</li>
              <li>• Help enrolling in coverage</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Find a Health Center</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <a
                href="https://findahealthcenter.hrsa.gov"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >findahealthcenter.hrsa.gov</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• Call 211 for local resources</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Bay Area County Contacts -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Bay Area County Health Offices
          </h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">San Francisco</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Human Services Agency<br />1235 Mission St<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:415-557-5000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">415-557-5000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Alameda County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:510-268-2000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">510-268-2000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Santa Clara County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:408-758-3800"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">408-758-3800</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Contra Costa County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Employment & Human Services<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:877-505-4630"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">877-505-4630</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Final Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Important Notice:</strong> The information on this page is for general guidance only.
            Program requirements, income limits, and benefits change periodically. This is not a guarantee
            of eligibility or benefits. The only way to determine if you qualify is to apply directly
            to the relevant program. We encourage you to contact your county office or a certified enrollment
            counselor for personalized assistance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Back Link -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <a href="/eligibility" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg
              class="w-4 h-4 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
            </svg>
            Back to Eligibility Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
